From Jack Stephenson Subject Re What is this file From article by John Wallace I've got this animation file with a What is this Are there anu MS DOS or OS programs which will run this file The GL file is an archive containing individual frames or pieces of frames usually stored as or files fonts and a file that tells the GRASP animation system how to display GL stands for Grasp There is probably a detailed discussion of this subject in the There are freely distributable viewers for GL files and they are usually named GRASPRT replace the with a version digit or letter Most GL files contain frames that are hardware specific to particular modes of the CGA EGA or VGA adapters on I think that there are some copies of GRASPRT available by anonymous ftp I know that I got one there a long time ago Good Luck Jack Jack Stephenson main e mail Racal Datacom alternate e mail Box Lauderdale FL USA Phone